Kazakhstan to Introduce ‘People’s IPOs’ Around October, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-20T01:40:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/kazakhstan-to-introduce-people-s-ipos-around-october-ft-says.html
Kazakhstan Economic Development
Minister  Kairat Kelimbetov  said the country would launch its
planned “people’s IPOs” of state-owned companies around
October, with the first offering in the last quarter of the
year, the Financial Times reported, citing an interview.  According to the plan, the government will offer discounted
minority stakes in the companies to ordinary citizens, the FT
said, citing Kelimbetov.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 